 the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":0,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":35,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":66,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":91,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":104,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Somerton Esquire was born about 1224, in Norfolk, England as the son of Somerton and Mrs Somerton. He married Mrs Robert Somerton before 1250, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1224–":"umbes 1224–Surnud","1224–Male":"1224–Surnud","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1228":"1228","1315":"1315","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","before 1224":"enne 1224","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","about 1224":"umbes 1224","before 1250":"enne 1250","1250":"1250","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"England","Somerton, Norfolk, England":"Somerton, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1224–":"noin 1224–Kuollut","1224–Male":"1224–Kuollut","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1228":"1228","1315":"1315","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","before 1224":"ennen vuotta 1224","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","about 1224":"noin 1224","before 1250":"ennen vuotta 1250","1250":"1250","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"England","Somerton, Norfolk, England":"Somerton, Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"about 1224–":"environ 1224–Décédé","1224–Male":"1224–Décédé","1228–Female":"1228–Décédée","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1228":"1228","1315":"1315","Abt 1250":"environ 1250","before 1224":"avant 1224","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","about 1224":"environ 1224","before 1250":"avant 1250","1250":"1250","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Somerton, Norfolk, England":"Somerton, Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Somerton Esquire est né environ 1224, à Norfolk, Angleterre, fils de Somerton et Mrs Somerton. Il a épousé Mrs Robert Somerton avant 1250, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1224–":"um